PEKIN - A 17-year-old Pekin High School Senior died after collapsing in a school hallway Wednesday morning. Hanna Holder was pronounced dead in the Pekin Hospital Emergency Room around 7:30 a.m.
An autopsy will be conducted tomorrow; no foul play is suspected, Tazewell County Coroner Dennis Conover said.

This is the sixth death of a Pekin High School student thus far this school year. Five others died in car accidents in September and October.

"I don't know of anybody in any school who's grieved as much in a school year as we have at Pekin High," Superintendent Paula Davis said.
